.TH "grk_dump" "1" "" "Version 10.0" "dump JPEG 2000 code stream to stdout or to file"
.SH NAME
grk_dump \- dump JPEG 2000 code stream to stdout or to file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]grk_dump\f[R] [\f[B]\-i\f[R] infile.jp2]
.SH DESCRIPTION
This program dumps the header and/or codestream of a JPEG 2000 file to
stdout or to a file.
.PP
\f[B]Important note on command line argument notation below\f[R]: the
outer square braces appear for clarity only, and \f[B]should not\f[R] be
included in the actual command line argument.
Square braces appearing inside the outer braces \f[B]should\f[R] be
included.
.SS Options
\f[CR]\-h\f[R]
.PP
Print a help message and exit.
.PP
\f[CR]\-\-help\f[R]
.PP
Show detailed usage.
.PP
\f[CR]\-i, \-\-input [file]\f[R]
.PP
Input file.
Required if \f[CR]\-\-batch\-src\f[R] option is not provided.
.PP
\f[CR]\-o, \-\-output [file]\f[R]
.PP
Output file.
Default: stdout.
.PP
\f[CR]\-y, \-\-batch\-src [directory]\f[R]
.PP
Path to image files directory.
Required if \f[CR]\-i\f[R] option is not provided.
.PP
\f[CR]\-f, \-\-flag [value]\f[R]
.PP
Flag value.
Default: \f[CR]0\f[R].
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]0\f[R] : dump header only
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]1\f[R] : dump codestream only
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]2\f[R] : dump both header and codestream
